{
  "doc_id": "40927",
  "text": "Poels et al [CITATION_1] reported severe BPVT in a 69-year-old female presenting with progressive dyspnea and syncope 9 months following TAVR (Edwards-Sapien 23-mm prosthesis) who was successfully treated with bioprosthetic MVR. Laboratory studies revealed a heterozygote prothrombin gene mutation causing a hypercoagulable state with a strongly increased factor VIII; she was therefore treated with aspirin and warfarin.",
  "correct_citation": {
